{"metadata":{"title":"Vector Tile Sources","roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/DDSCircleLayerExample","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Add and style a vector tile source"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/AnimatedLineExample","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/WebAPIDataExample","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/LineStyleLayerExample","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/POIAlongRouteExample","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/GeoJSON","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/PMTiles"],"generated":true,"title":"Styling and Dynamic Data","anchor":"Styling-and-Dynamic-Data"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This example uses UIKit","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This example shows how a vector data source can be added and a style for it can be configured dynamically.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The tiles are ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/demotiles\/tree\/gh-pages\/tiles-omt","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" that use the OpenMapTiles schema. We are interested in the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/openmaptiles.org\/schema\/#poi","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" that are in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poi"},{"text":" layer, and filter this further with an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSPredicate"},{"text":" to only show POIs with a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":" of shop. Each POI has a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rank"},{"text":" which is normally used to reduce label density. In this example, we use it to demonstrate how a numeric attribute can be used for styling with the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/maplibre.org\/maplibre-style-spec\/expressions\/#step","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" expression. POIs with a rank between 0 and 10 get a red color, between 10 and 20 green, etc.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["class DDSCircleLayerExample: UIViewController, MLNMapViewDelegate {","    var mapView: MLNMapView!","","    override func viewDidLoad() {","        super.viewDidLoad()","","        mapView = MLNMapView(frame: view.bounds, styleURL: AMERICANA_STYLE)","        mapView.autoresizingMask = [.flexibleWidth, .flexibleHeight]","        mapView.tintColor = .darkGray","","        \/\/ Set the map’s center coordinate and zoom level.","        let innsbruck = CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: 47.26497, longitude: 11.4088)","        mapView.setCenter(innsbruck, animated: false)","        mapView.zoomLevel = 14","","        mapView.delegate = self","        view.addSubview(mapView)","    }","","    \/\/ Wait until the style is loaded before modifying the map style.","    func mapView(_: MLNMapView, didFinishLoading style: MLNStyle) {","        let source = MLNVectorTileSource(identifier: \"demotiles\", configurationURL: URL(string: \"https:\/\/demotiles.maplibre.org\/tiles-omt\/tiles.json\")!)","","        style.addSource(source)","","        let layer = MLNCircleStyleLayer(identifier: \"poi-shop-style\", source: source)","","        layer.sourceLayerIdentifier = \"poi\"","        layer.predicate = NSPredicate(format: \"class == %@\", \"shop\")","","        \/\/ Style the circle layer color based on the rank","        layer.circleColor = NSExpression(mglJSONObject: [\"step\", [\"get\", \"rank\"], 0, \"red\", 10, \"green\", 20, \"blue\", 30, \"purple\", 40, \"yellow\"] as [Any])","        layer.circleRadius = NSExpression(forConstantValue: 3)","","        style.addLayer(layer)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"DDSCircleLayerExample.png","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Map data from OpenStreetMap. Style uses OpenMapTiles."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre-native-for-ios\/ddscirclelayerexample"]}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS/AnimatedLineExample":{"type":"topic","role":"article","title":"Animated Line","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre-native-for-ios\/animatedlineexample","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/AnimatedLineExample","abstract":[{"text":"Add an animated line to a map","type":"text"}]},"https://maplibre.org/maplibre-style-spec/expressions/#step":{"url":"https:\/\/maplibre.org\/maplibre-style-spec\/expressions\/#step","identifier":"https:\/\/maplibre.org\/maplibre-style-spec\/expressions\/#step","type":"link","title":"step","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"step"}]},"https://github.com/maplibre/demotiles/tree/gh-pages/tiles-omt":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/demotiles\/tree\/gh-pages\/tiles-omt","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/demotiles\/tree\/gh-pages\/tiles-omt","type":"link","title":"tiles around Innsbruck, Austria","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"tiles around Innsbruck, Austria"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS/LineStyleLayerExample":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Adding an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNLineStyleLayer"},{"type":"text","text":" to the map using a GeoJSON file."}],"title":"Using GeoJSON with a line style layer","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre-native-for-ios\/linestylelayerexample","type":"topic","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/LineStyleLayerExample"},"DDSCircleLayerExample.png":{"identifier":"DDSCircleLayerExample.png","type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["2x","light"],"url":"\/images\/org.swift.MyProject\/DDSCircleLayerExample@2x.png"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"role":"collection","title":"MapLibre","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS/WebAPIDataExample":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/WebAPIDataExample","title":"Showing data from an API","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre-native-for-ios\/webapidataexample","type":"topic","role":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Showing data from an API with custom styling and interaction","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNLineStyleLayer":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNLineStyleLayer","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNLineStyleLayer"},{"type":"text","text":" is a style layer that renders one or more stroked"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polylines on the map."}],"fragments":[{"text":"MLNLineStyleLayer","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnlinestylelayer","title":"MLNLineStyleLayer"},"ht